author: dlr
msg: * subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/util.c
(parsed_request): Always send the Accept-Language header as part of
the request to communicate our language preference to the server.
mod_dav_svn doesn't yet do anything with this information (though
is likely to eventually), but other modules may.

author: pburba
msg: Port of svn switch via file:/// for OS/400.
Disable the --diff3-cmd option as we have no plans to support that in the port.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/main.c
(svn_cl__cmd_table): Disable --diff3-cmd for svn switch.

author: pburba
msg: Port of svn copy via file:/// for OS/400.
* subversion/libsvn_client/copy.c
(DOT_TMP_STR): New ascii escaped symbolic constant.
(repos_to_wc_copy): Replace string literal with new symbol above.

author: pburba
msg: Fix two ebcdic port specific bugs.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/util.c
(svn_cl__make_log_msg_baton): Check for NULL opt_state->message before
converting to utf-8.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/ebcdic.c
(svn_ebcdic_set_file_ccsid):  Follow-up to r14841: Single quotes are valid in
iSeries filenames, double quotes are not, so the qsh setccsid command must be
setccsid CCSID "filename" rather than setccsid CCSID 'filename' to avoid
potential mismatched quotes.

author: lundblad
